      "source": "### Typical 2. Savings Projection (3 Years)\n\nCompute final savings after 3 years given:\n- Save £10 every week for 3 years\n- Year 1 bonus: +£20 each week\n- Every 2 weeks: −£0.50 (sister)\nAssume 52 weeks per year; use arithmetic and augmented assignment; no conditionals.\n\n**Example Output:**\n```\nFinal savings after 3 years: £4689.50\n```\n",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "81904cff",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "# Your code here\n\nweekly_saving = 10\nbonus_year1 = 20\nsister_deduction = 0.50\nweeks_per_year = 52\nyears = 3\n\n# Year 1 total\nyear1_saving = weeks_per_year * (weekly_saving + bonus_year1) - (weeks_per_year / 2) * sister_deduction\n\n# Years 2 & 3 total\nother_years_saving = (years - 1) * (weeks_per_year * weekly_saving - (weeks_per_year / 2) * sister_deduction)\n\n# Final savings\ntotal_savings = year1_saving + other_years_saving\n\n\nprint(f\"Final savings after 3 years: £{total_savings:.2f}\")",
      "metadata": {
        "trusted": true
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": "Final savings after 3 years: £2561.00\n"
        }
      ],
      "execution_count": 6
